<seg id=1> Primary and Secondary School Children Go to School As Usual in the Disaster Area of Zhejiang </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Hangzhou, September 2 (Xinhua News Agency) Typhoon 17th brought great losses to the education system of Zhejiang, with buildings and facilities of over 1,500 schools damaged. </seg>
<seg id=3> After disaster-relief efforts by the local governments and people, most primary and secondary schools have restored order. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The education authority of Zhejiang sent out working groups to Wenzhou and Taizhou and other places to help restoring the education work in the disaster-stricken areas. </seg>
<seg id=5> The Wenzhou education authority sent over 20 of their staff to go to Leqing/Ouhai/Dongtou/Pingyang and other places in seven groups, to help repair damanged school buildings and prepare for new school year. 200,000 yuan was allocated from education fund to help the disaster-hit education to restore to normal. </seg>
<seg id=6> Local education authorities and administrations in the disaster areas made it a policy that students whose families were affected by the Typhoon and could not afford the tuition can enjoy a certain degree of tuition waiver or scholarship, so that they can go to school as usual. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> School leaders and staff in the disaster areas go to school earlier than usual to clean up and do sterilization and repair jobs by themselves </seg>
<seg id=8> Wenzhou city government and Youth League unite with the teachers and students of the disaster areas to make donations for the schools hit by the disaster. By now, they have received donations from all walks of society up to over 1 million yuan. </seg>
</p>
